import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Easy Chat Maker"
  description="How Easy Chat Maker handles your data: chats stay in your browser, no account required. Details on cookies, advertising and analytics."
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  updated="July 11, 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains what information Easy Chat Maker ("we", "our", or "the site")
    collects when you use our website and chat mockup editor, and how we handle it. The short
    version: <strong>we designed this tool so your content never has to leave your browser.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information you create in the editor</h2>
  <p>
    Conversations, names, avatars and images you add in the editor are stored <strong>locally in
    your browser</strong> (using localStorage and IndexedDB) so your work is still there when you
    come back. This content is <strong>not uploaded to our servers</strong>, and we cannot see it.
    Clearing your browser data removes it permanently.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information we collect automatically</h2>
  <p>
    Like most websites, we may collect basic technical information when you visit, such as your
    IP address, browser type, device type, pages visited and time spent on the site. This data is
    aggregated and used only to understand how the site is used and to improve it.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
  <p>
    We use cookies and similar technologies (such as localStorage) to remember your work in the
    editor and to measure site usage. You can control or delete cookies through your browser
    settings; the editor will still work, but saved chats may be lost.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Advertising</h2>
  <p>
    We may display advertising, including ads served by <strong>Google AdSense</strong>. Google
    and its partners use advertising cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and
    other websites.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits
      to this website or other websites.
    </li>
    <li>
      Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based
      on your visits to this site and/or other sites on the Internet.
    </li>
    <li>
      You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener nofollow">Google Ads Settings</a>,
      or opt out of some third-party vendors' use of cookies at
      <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" rel="noopener nofollow">www.aboutads.info</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We may use privacy-respecting analytics services to understand aggregate site traffic. These
    services do not receive the content you create in the editor.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
    information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us personal
    information, please contact us and we will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct or delete personal data
    we hold about you. Because the content you create never reaches our servers, most data is
    under your direct control in your browser. For anything else, contact us and we will help.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an
    updated date at the top.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy? Reach us via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
